Predicted changes in the effective number of relativistic neutrino species, Neff, as a function of a fractional variation in the input parameter p, with all other inputs held fixed at their fiducial values. The slope near the fiducial point defines the local logarithmic response ∂ln(Neff)/∂lnp used to build the sensitivity matrix and propagate theory uncertainties. Thermonuclear reaction rates are not included, as varying them has no effect on Neff.
